PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F446A1777190772
OL,3,C'Most likely' Noah Donohoe entered
OL,4,Ctunnel through bars of culvert entrance
OL,6,FEarlier, Mr Coll read agreed facts and
OL,7,Fa statement from witness C4, who said
OL,8,Fhe had no interaction with Noah on
OL,9,FJune 21 2020 and "had nothing to do"
OL,10,Fwith his disappearance.
OL,12,FC4's statement also said that he had
OL,13,Fno knowledge of speculation that Noah
OL,14,Fhad been injected with drugs.
OL,16,FMr Coll said C4 had previously been
OL,17,Fgiven properly interested person (PIP)
OL,18,Fstatus at the inquest, but based on
OL,19,Fthe agreed facts he was not required
OL,20,Fto attend to give evidence and his PIP
OL,21,Fstatus was being withdrawn.
OL,26,@qD@ROUqD@dO]
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}           G10/11
